Gov. Ifeanyi Ugwuanyi of Enugu State has appointed Mr Nzekwe Manfred as the new Commissioner for Youths and Sport, NAN reports. Mr Dan Onwuegbuna, the Public Relations Officer of the State Ministry of Youths and Sports, made this known to newsmen in Enugu on Thursday. According to him, Manfred was the former Executive Chairman of Oji River Local Government Council of the state. He said, “Manfred was a former Director of Enugu State Tourism Board and Special Personal Assistant (SPA) to Governor Ifeanyi Ugwuanyi on Culture and Tourism. ”I believe that he will use his vast experience to galvanize youths of Enugu State and propel sports development in the state. ”We welcome him on board in his aspiration to contribute to the development of youths and sports in the state.”